HEADWORD: Consecrator
<hw>Con"se*cra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<def>One who consecrates; one who performs the rites by which a person
or thing is devoted or dedicated to sacred purposes.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>consecrater</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consecratory</ent>⟦br⟧
